# Local clasp ignore list — used by the Google Apps Script CLI (clasp).
# This file lists files that should not be pushed with `clasp push` and
# is typically local-only. Keeping it out of source control avoids
# accidental commits of machine-specific ignores.
.claspignore

# Local clasp config / metadata. Contains project identifiers and
# environment-specific info (script IDs, deploy IDs, or local auth).
# Do not commit if you want to avoid leaking deploy IDs or local state.
.clasp.json

# VS Code workspace settings and extensions. These are personal or
# machine-specific (editor settings, launch configs, recommended
# extensions) and commonly omitted from the repository.
.vscode/

# Google Apps Script project manifest (appsscript.json).
# This file can be generated by the Apps Script editor and sometimes
# contains environment-specific configuration. It's ignored here to
# prevent overwriting remote project settings; remove this line if
# you intend to version-control your manifest.
appsscript.json

# macOS Finder metadata files — safe to ignore. These are created by
# Finder in directories and can clutter diffs across macOS machines.
.DS_Store

# -----------------------------
# Common editor / IDE folders
# -----------------------------
# Visual Studio Code workspace settings (already present above but keep trailing slash style)
.vscode/

# JetBrains IDEs (IntelliJ, WebStorm, etc.)
.idea/

# -----------------------------
# OS-specific files
# -----------------------------
# macOS Finder metadata (already added)
# Thumbs.db for Windows Explorer
Thumbs.db

# -----------------------------
# Node / build artifacts
# -----------------------------
# If you use local tooling (npm, webpack, rollup) to build client-side code
# or manage dependencies, ignore node_modules and common build folders.
node_modules/
dist/
build/

# -----------------------------
# Environment / secrets / logs
# -----------------------------
# Local environment files and temporary logs. Keep credentials out of Git.
.env
.env.local
*.log

# -----------------------------
# clasp / Apps Script helpers
# -----------------------------
# Sometimes projects include helper folders or generated files (e.g. `lib/`,
# `out/`) from transpilers or bundlers used before `clasp push` — ignore
# them if they are build outputs.
lib/
out/

# -----------------------------
# Optional: global gitignore recommendation
# -----------------------------
# You may prefer to add `.DS_Store`, OS files and editor folders to a global
# gitignore (see `git config --global core.excludesfile ~/.gitignore_global`).
